<i>or if Carrie wants her</i>
<i>to be for real.</i>

01:40.361 --> 01:41.428
The way I am now,
I wouldn't trust me either.

01:41.462 --> 01:43.130
But the Carrie
who recruited her,

01:43.164 --> 01:44.164
that one I believe.

01:48.571 --> 01:52.942
(speaking Arabic)

01:52.976 --> 01:54.076
BRODY:
Hi, Roya.

01:54.111 --> 01:55.311
Congressman Brody.

01:55.345 --> 01:57.780
I'm a friend of Nazir's.

01:57.814 --> 02:00.550
I will not help you in the
killing of innocent civilians.

02:00.585 --> 02:02.219
I met a young man yesterday.

02:02.253 --> 02:03.887
Lost both his arms in Iraq.

02:03.922 --> 02:05.856
They have a
fund-raiser coming up,

02:05.891 --> 02:07.892
and I thought that we
could host it together.

02:07.927 --> 02:10.461
Red Team Two, fire discipline
is two shots each.

02:10.496 --> 02:11.830
Targets are two in robes.

02:11.864 --> 02:13.431
ESTES:
<i>Holy shit, it's him.</i>

02:16.069 --> 02:17.069
Fire.

02:20.140 --> 02:21.207
Somebody warned him.

02:21.241 --> 02:22.575
BRODY:
<i>I'm a congressman.</i>

02:22.609 --> 02:24.744
I cannot be texting
secret messages

02:24.778 --> 02:26.513
while I am surrounded by
the fucking Joint Chiefs.

02:26.547 --> 02:28.048
- Is anyone in the apartment?
- No.

02:28.082 --> 02:29.049
- Give me your keys.
SAUL: - Carrie.

02:29.083 --> 02:30.050
We just missed Abu Nazir.

02:30.084 --> 02:31.485
Get in the car.
Back in the car!

02:31.519 --> 02:32.920
We can't leave here without
getting what's in there.

02:35.991 --> 02:38.326
(gunshot)

02:39.928 --> 02:41.162
Carrie.
(Carrie screams)

02:41.196 --> 02:42.196
I got you.

02:50.272 --> 02:51.773
My name is Nicholas Brody.

02:51.807 --> 02:53.108
By the time you watch this,

02:53.142 --> 02:55.177
you'll have read
a lot of things about me.

03:16.232 --> 03:18.232
(speaking Arabic)

03:24.907 --> 03:27.542
This way. Now.

03:27.576 --> 03:30.044
(speaking Arabic)

03:31.480 --> 03:35.616
That briefcase is clearly
marked as a diplomatic bag.

03:35.651 --> 03:36.751
Do not open it.

03:36.785 --> 03:37.885
Key please.

03:42.291 --> 03:43.625
Saul Berenson.

03:43.659 --> 03:45.527
Jewish, yes?

03:47.596 --> 03:49.064
American.

03:54.204 --> 03:57.139
A Lebanese security official

03:57.173 --> 03:58.941
must know better
than to do that

03:58.975 --> 04:02.411
unless he's actually
working for someone else.

04:02.445 --> 04:04.913
Like, say, Hezbollah.

04:28.270 --> 04:30.004
If you don't put that back

04:30.038 --> 04:31.439
and allow me
to continue to my flight,

04:31.473 --> 04:33.507
you'll be the
cause of a serious

04:33.541 --> 04:35.909
diplomatic incident
with the United States.

04:37.979 --> 04:39.880
So, please, take a moment.

04:39.914 --> 04:41.514
Think carefully.
(locks briefcase)

04:46.554 --> 04:48.888
Never come back to Lebanon.

05:04.940 --> 05:08.109
WOMAN: Sir, I need you
to put the briefcase

05:08.143 --> 05:10.077
in the overhead bin
for takeoff, please.

05:10.112 --> 05:11.712
I'll do it.
Just give me a second.

05:40.976 --> 05:43.245
(crickets chirping)

05:43.279 --> 05:45.280
(jazz music playing)

05:50.352 --> 05:51.819
(snaps fingers)

05:51.854 --> 05:53.922
- Jesus, Dad, what?
- What the hell are you doing?

05:53.956 --> 05:56.725
Do you even know
what time it is?

05:56.759 --> 05:57.726
I'm writing a report.

05:57.760 --> 05:59.160
At 3:20 a.m.?

05:59.195 --> 06:01.029
What? Have you been up
all night doing this?

06:01.063 --> 06:03.432
You need to put this
away, and go to sleep.

06:03.466 --> 06:05.433
I can't. Not yet.
I have to get this done,

06:05.468 --> 06:07.736
- and it has to be done right.
- For crying out loud.

06:07.770 --> 06:10.305
Carrie, you have a disease.

06:10.339 --> 06:12.674
Dad, please, not now.

06:12.709 --> 06:14.943
And in case you've
forgotten what I know,

06:14.978 --> 06:17.112
your doctor has told you
a million times... sleep

06:17.147 --> 06:19.148
is one of the most,
if not the most important...

06:19.182 --> 06:20.315
I know.

06:20.350 --> 06:23.285
I know. I'm nearly finished.
I promise.

06:23.319 --> 06:24.453
How much longer?

06:24.487 --> 06:26.989
(sighs) Two hours, max.

06:27.023 --> 06:28.891
One. One more hour.

06:28.925 --> 06:30.325
- Fine.
- You can't

06:30.360 --> 06:32.027
do this to yourself anymore,
sweetheart.

06:32.062 --> 06:33.462
You just can't.

06:33.496 --> 06:35.531
I'm okay.

06:35.565 --> 06:38.001
In fact, I feel pretty great.

06:38.035 --> 06:40.803
Wired is what you are.

06:40.838 --> 06:43.039
There's a difference.

06:45.376 --> 06:46.809
Point taken.

06:46.844 --> 06:48.044
One more hour.

06:50.080 --> 06:51.681
One more.

07:28.321 --> 07:31.156
Sorry. It was just, it was here
on the table and, uh...

07:31.190 --> 07:33.759
And just jumped out at you?

07:33.793 --> 07:35.261
Well, I know how much

07:35.295 --> 07:36.962
you hate talking
about this stuff in public.

07:36.996 --> 07:38.530
Um, I was just curious

07:38.565 --> 07:40.832
what you were planning
to say tonight.

07:40.867 --> 07:43.335
What do you think?

07:45.972 --> 07:47.939
"By my third year in captivity,

07:47.974 --> 07:50.875
I knew that this was
where I was gonna die,

07:50.909 --> 07:53.812
that I had to accept that,

07:53.846 --> 07:55.747
make peace with it,
so that's what I did.

07:55.781 --> 07:57.482
I prepared to die."

08:03.456 --> 08:05.824
"But I didn't die.

08:05.858 --> 08:08.593
Somehow I got to come home
to a wife and two kids

08:08.628 --> 08:11.363
I'd talked myself into
believing would be just fine,

08:11.397 --> 08:12.831
no, better off,

08:12.866 --> 08:15.300
without me.

08:15.334 --> 08:17.903
I mean how could they
really know me anymore?"

08:27.114 --> 08:29.615
Too much?

08:29.650 --> 08:31.784
Well, it's just...

08:31.819 --> 08:35.154
it's the first time
I've ever heard it.

08:35.188 --> 08:37.590
I, um...

08:37.625 --> 08:40.426
I never knew this is
how you felt.

08:40.461 --> 08:42.028
Yeah.

08:42.062 --> 08:44.363
You're right. I don't
really like talking about it.

08:44.398 --> 08:46.299
- Brody.
- What?

08:46.333 --> 08:47.600
Look...

08:47.635 --> 08:49.635
I didn't mean...

08:49.670 --> 08:50.970
It's okay, Jess.
It's all right.

08:51.004 --> 08:52.705
No, no, no, it's not.

08:52.740 --> 08:54.040
Hey...

08:54.074 --> 08:56.475
I know you're doing
this event for me.

08:56.509 --> 08:58.911
I want you to know
I appreciate it.

09:04.117 --> 09:06.552
Thank you.

09:22.803 --> 09:24.070
Hey, Jess, wait, wait.

09:24.104 --> 09:25.471
Wait.

09:25.506 --> 09:26.739
Seriously?

09:26.774 --> 09:29.843
You want me to stop?

09:34.915 --> 09:36.916
No.

09:44.325 --> 09:46.359
Follow me.

09:46.393 --> 09:48.127
Hey.

09:54.401 --> 09:56.402
Brody...

09:56.437 --> 09:58.537
Slow down, slow down.

10:01.474 --> 10:03.842
Look at me.

10:03.877 --> 10:05.210
Go slow.

10:25.265 --> 10:27.166
Yeah.

10:27.200 --> 10:29.769
Like that.

10:36.776 --> 10:39.244
Yeah.

10:39.278 --> 10:41.279
(door opens)

10:50.556 --> 10:52.857
Hey, aren't you
home early today?

10:54.227 --> 10:55.427
Teacher's conference day.

10:55.462 --> 10:57.997
What's your excuse?

10:58.031 --> 10:59.398
- Hey.
JESSICA: - Xander.

10:59.433 --> 11:00.933
Day off at your school, too?

11:00.968 --> 11:02.901
Coincidence, huh?

11:02.936 --> 11:04.503
Or maybe not.

11:04.537 --> 11:07.172
I already graduated
last year. It's all good.

11:07.206 --> 11:08.740
DANA:
So, uh...

11:08.774 --> 11:10.107
slow day in Congress, Dad?

11:10.142 --> 11:11.942
- Or...
- Don't you have

11:11.977 --> 11:14.278
- homework to do?
- I already did it.

11:14.312 --> 11:16.313
(phone buzzes)

11:20.618 --> 11:22.019
(clears throat)

11:22.053 --> 11:24.421
It's work trying
to get a hold of me.

11:26.224 --> 11:27.457
DANA:
Is that the cup

11:27.492 --> 11:29.292
that Chris made for Dad?

11:29.327 --> 11:31.161
Shit.

11:34.332 --> 11:35.232
I got your text.

11:35.266 --> 11:36.867
We have a problem and no time,

11:36.901 --> 11:38.802
so please just listen.

11:38.836 --> 11:40.904
The CIA are in the middle
of processing intelligence

11:40.938 --> 11:42.572
from their operation in Beirut.

11:42.607 --> 11:43.941
They're very close
to finding out

11:43.975 --> 11:45.609
about our friend in Gettysburg.

11:45.643 --> 11:46.810
The Tailor?

11:46.844 --> 11:48.045
You need to go there now

11:48.079 --> 11:49.446
and move him to a safe house,

11:49.481 --> 11:51.081
60 miles further west.

11:51.115 --> 11:53.116
Well, why don't you just call
him and tell him to move?

11:53.151 --> 11:54.651
Because I might unnerve him
unnecessarily.

11:54.685 --> 11:56.820
He needs to be looked
in the eye and reassured

11:56.855 --> 11:58.255
that he's in safe hands.

11:58.289 --> 11:59.756
Why me? Why not you?

11:59.790 --> 12:01.458
Because he doesn't know me.
He knows you.

12:01.492 --> 12:03.093
You're the only one he knows.

12:03.127 --> 12:04.761
How can you be sure the CIA
hasn't already sent

12:04.796 --> 12:06.630
- somebody out there?
- Because I'm sure.

12:06.664 --> 12:07.931
They found an e-mail
that mentions

12:07.965 --> 12:09.566
a contact in Gettysburg.
They're only just now

12:09.600 --> 12:11.701
putting together a list
of suspects in the area.

12:11.736 --> 12:13.303
Is there a problem, Nicholas?

12:13.337 --> 12:15.272
Yeah, I'd say there's
a fucking problem.

12:20.010 --> 12:23.779
I am giving a speech at a dinner
for wounded veterans tonight,

12:23.814 --> 12:26.983
in D.C. which
the vice president is attending.

12:27.017 --> 12:29.819
If you go there now,
you'll make it back easily.

12:29.854 --> 12:31.355
You move him
as fast as possible.

12:31.389 --> 12:33.023
I don't believe this.

12:33.057 --> 12:34.525
Must I remind you,
he's the one man

12:34.559 --> 12:35.793
who knows the truth about you?

12:35.828 --> 12:37.128
(sighs)

12:37.162 --> 12:39.464
Take the Tailor to 124 Mount
Chapel Road, Somerset.

12:39.498 --> 12:41.500
The key's in the
bird feeder on the tree

12:41.534 --> 12:43.435
to the right of the garage,
around back.

12:43.469 --> 12:45.036
Repeat the address back to me.

12:45.071 --> 12:47.806
124 Mount Chapel Road, Somerset.

12:54.814 --> 12:56.816
(doorbell rings)

12:59.219 --> 13:00.919
Can I help you?

13:00.954 --> 13:02.788
Hello, Mr. Mathison.
Is Carrie here?

13:02.823 --> 13:04.190
CARRIE:
Oh, I got it.

13:04.224 --> 13:05.324
Hey, Danny.

13:05.359 --> 13:07.226
FRANK:
CIA never heard of e-mail?

13:07.260 --> 13:09.061
Uh, you making eggs, Dad?

13:09.096 --> 13:10.229
It's lunchtime.

13:10.264 --> 13:11.831
A sandwich then.

13:11.865 --> 13:13.466
Sure.

13:13.500 --> 13:15.034
CARRIE:
Hey, Danny. Sorry about that.

13:15.068 --> 13:16.402
DANNY:
How you doing, Carrie?

13:16.436 --> 13:17.669
I'm good.

13:17.704 --> 13:18.904
- Is that it?
- Yep.

13:18.938 --> 13:20.673
- All 18 pages.
- I'll get this

13:20.707 --> 13:22.041
to everybody right away.

13:22.075 --> 13:23.209
What time is
the debrief with the group?

13:23.243 --> 13:25.211
- Uh, scheduled for 6:00.
- So late?

13:25.245 --> 13:28.080
Estes is at an emergency
threat level briefing all day.

13:28.114 --> 13:30.216
- What's going on?
- Um, nothing specific.

13:30.250 --> 13:33.019
Yet. But the top brass
huddle every single day now.

13:33.053 --> 13:34.653
Hey, can I say...

13:34.688 --> 13:36.389
what you just did
in the field--

13:36.423 --> 13:38.524
was pretty damn impressive.

13:38.558 --> 13:40.125
Thanks, Danny.

13:40.160 --> 13:41.827
I appreciate that.

13:41.862 --> 13:44.363
- I'll text you later to confirm
the 6:00 p.m. debrief. - Thanks.

13:44.397 --> 13:46.399
I look forward to it.

13:51.605 --> 13:53.573
Pickle on your sandwich?

14:02.214 --> 14:04.215
(birds chirping)

14:33.478 --> 14:35.478
(cash register chatters)

14:45.991 --> 14:47.959
(door bell jingles)

14:50.262 --> 14:52.230
<i>Assalamo Allaikum.</i>

14:54.433 --> 14:56.401
<i>Wa 'alaikum-as-salam.</i>

14:58.104 --> 14:59.638
- You.
- I need you to pack a bag.

14:59.672 --> 15:01.473
- Fast.
- Bag? What for?

15:01.507 --> 15:02.674
The CIA know about you.

15:02.709 --> 15:04.677
I gotta get you out of here.

15:05.946 --> 15:07.280
How do you know this?

15:07.314 --> 15:09.582
- I'll explain in the car. Hurry.
- No, tell me now.

15:09.617 --> 15:13.787
The CIA had an operation
in Beirut to kill Abu Nazir.

15:13.822 --> 15:15.956
He escaped,
but they found intelligence

15:15.991 --> 15:17.958
that may lead to you.

15:18.960 --> 15:21.261
- Where are you taking me?
- To a safe house.

15:21.295 --> 15:22.996
How do you know it's safe?

15:23.031 --> 15:25.299
Hey, all I know is
you're not safe here anymore.

15:25.333 --> 15:27.100
Who sent you?

15:27.135 --> 15:28.435
Look, I'm here to help you.

15:28.470 --> 15:29.803
Get a bag, let's go.

15:37.545 --> 15:39.079
Fuck.

15:39.114 --> 15:40.514
Forget the bag. Go.

15:40.548 --> 15:41.682
Go!

15:46.054 --> 15:48.055
Okay, walk.

15:49.924 --> 15:52.092
Get in the car.

15:52.127 --> 15:54.128
Don't make me say it twice.

16:13.113 --> 16:15.080
(tires screech)

16:28.795 --> 16:31.430
CARRIE: Bob kisses his wife
and children good-bye.

16:31.464 --> 16:34.532
ESL STUDENTS: Bob kisses his
wife and children good-bye.

16:34.566 --> 16:38.102
Uh, Bob drives to work
in a red car.

16:38.136 --> 16:40.537
STUDENTS: Bob drives
to work in a red car.

16:41.573 --> 16:45.376
Are you okay, Miss Carrie?

16:45.410 --> 16:46.777
I'm s...
What, Lulu?

16:46.811 --> 16:47.778
What's wrong?

16:47.812 --> 16:50.214
No text from boyfriend, eh?

16:50.248 --> 16:53.016
(students laugh)

16:53.051 --> 16:55.252
GALVEZ (on phone):
Hi, this is Danny Galvez.

16:55.286 --> 16:56.820
Please leave a message.
(beep)

16:56.855 --> 16:57.821
Danny, it's Carrie.

16:57.856 --> 16:59.323
Uh, it's nearly 5:00,

16:59.357 --> 17:01.725
and I never heard back
about the debrief, so...

17:01.759 --> 17:03.427
I'm heading out now.

17:03.461 --> 17:05.929
Uh... call if
anything's changed.

17:05.963 --> 17:07.931
Thanks.

17:11.234 --> 17:14.604
What happens when we get there?

17:14.637 --> 17:16.772
I drop you off. You wait.

17:16.808 --> 17:17.973
They said that?

17:18.009 --> 17:19.943
I'm guessing.

17:19.977 --> 17:21.144
So you don't know?

17:21.178 --> 17:23.713
It's an educated guess.

17:23.747 --> 17:25.915
I wait for what?

17:25.949 --> 17:29.785
Well, I imagine they want to
get you out of the country

17:29.820 --> 17:31.387
as fast as possible.

17:31.421 --> 17:33.288
You imagine. You guess.

17:33.323 --> 17:35.024
Take a breath.

17:36.159 --> 17:37.760
If it wasn't for me,
you'd probably be

17:37.794 --> 17:40.228
on your way to Guantanamo
by now.

17:40.263 --> 17:42.831
You think if they caught me
that I would talk?

17:42.865 --> 17:45.734
They're not gonna catch you now.

17:46.802 --> 17:48.970
You know what else
they didn't tell me?

17:49.004 --> 17:51.005
Your name.

17:55.946 --> 17:58.281
Suit yourself.

17:58.315 --> 17:59.950
We'll be there
in 30 or 40 minutes,

17:59.984 --> 18:01.918
and you'll be
somebody else's problem.

18:05.956 --> 18:07.924
Bassel.

18:09.961 --> 18:11.561
My name is Bassel.

18:14.432 --> 18:16.433
(wheel rattling,
tires screeching)

18:16.468 --> 18:17.668
(cursing in Arabic)

18:33.251 --> 18:35.420
Fuck.

18:42.128 --> 18:44.129
Oh, you gotta be shitting me.

18:46.799 --> 18:47.965
There's no fucking jack.

